cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with medical image classification using deep learning models and proposes a novel approach to utilize web data for training. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses transfer learning and loss functions, which are common topics in machine learning, specifically in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of search by image and web-crawling techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with modeling noise structure and incorporating it into the training process, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
